					<hr />
					<h3 class="mt-3 text-secondary font-italic font-weight-light">
						What is a contact management system?</h3>

					<p class="text-secondary font-italic p-4 paragraph">Contact
						management is the best solution to track and manage contacts as it
						will present relevant information in a clear way which will help
						you work efficiently. Contact management is a database with names,
						addresses, phone numbers, emails and all information regarding
						your contacts. You will be able to keep track of every contact,
						update details regularly and view past conversations you had with
						customers from a single platform. All members of your organization
						will be able to access contact management system through a
						centralized interface and have a clear view of each contact. You
						will have a complete record of phone calls and emails, set
						follow-up reminders and can add additional notes in reference to
						the conversation you had with any contact. This will help you to
						up-sell or cross-sell to your existing customers by recalling what
						products or services they loved.</p>

					<h3 class="mt-3 text-secondary font-italic font-weight-light">
						Benefits of using a contact management system</h3>

					<p class="text-secondary font-italic p-4 paragraph">There are
						many good features a contact management system has that can help
						you manage, organize and share contact information seamlessly. But
						the most common features a good contact management software must
						have is that it should be cloud-based, integrate easily with your
						commonly used applications, allow you to group contacts, add
						relevant notes and set reminders for meetings.</p>


